@page "/solutions/marketing"
@layout MarketingLayout

<PageTitle>NavTour for Marketing Teams &mdash; NavTour</PageTitle>
<HeadContent>
    <meta name="description" content="NavTour helps marketing teams replace static product screenshots with interactive demos on the website, in campaigns, and across every buyer-facing asset." />
</HeadContent>

<section class="nt-page-hero">
    <div class="nt-container">
        <span class="eyebrow">Solutions &middot; Marketing</span>
        <h1>Replace the explainer video<br />with a demo that <em>actually converts.</em></h1>
        <p class="lead">Embed a live NavTour on your homepage, in email campaigns, and on ad landing pages. Measurable intent from every visitor, zero engineering time.</p>
        <div class="nt-hero-actions">
            <a href="/register" class="btn btn-orange btn-lg">Start free &rarr;</a>
            <a href="/solutions" class="btn btn-outline btn-lg">All use cases</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="nt-frames-section">
    <div class="nt-container">
        <article class="nt-frame-row">
            <div class="nt-frame-copy">
                <div class="num">01<span class="slash">/</span><span class="lbl">Website hero</span></div>
                <h3>Your homepage demo is live in<br /><em>an afternoon, not a sprint.</em></h3>
                <p>Capture your product with the Chrome extension and embed the NavTour on your homepage. No video to re-record every release, no dev ticket to update the marketing site.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>One-line embed script, works in any CMS</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Auto-updates when you republish the demo</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Demo Hub for multi-product or multi-persona pages</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-frame-visual">
                <span class="nt-frame-cap">Website embed &middot; homepage hero</span>
                <div class="nt-frame-img">
                    <img src="/images/shots/hub.png" alt="NavTour demo hub embedded on a marketing site" class="nt-lightbox" />
                </div>
                <div class="anno tl">
                    <div class="lbl">No video, no stale screenshots</div>
                    <strong>Interactive from day one</strong>
                    <p>Visitors click through the real product, not a recording that&rsquo;s two releases behind.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

        <article class="nt-frame-row reverse">
            <div class="nt-frame-copy">
                <div class="num">02<span class="slash">/</span><span class="lbl">Campaigns</span></div>
                <h3>Gated demos that <em>capture intent</em> inside any campaign.</h3>
                <p>Gate any NavTour with a custom lead form — collect name, company, and role before the first step plays. All form data lands in HubSpot or Salesforce with the engagement timeline attached.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>No-code lead capture form, fully branded</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Native HubSpot, Salesforce, and Marketo sync</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Completion events as campaign conversion goals</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-frame-visual">
                <span class="nt-frame-cap">Lead form &middot; gated demo</span>
                <div class="nt-frame-img">
                    <img src="/images/shots/leads.png" alt="Lead capture form before a NavTour demo" class="nt-lightbox" />
                </div>
                <div class="anno br">
                    <div class="lbl">Intent, not just vanity metrics</div>
                    <strong>+38% demo-to-meeting conversion</strong>
                    <p>Median lift when a NavTour replaces a static LP for product-led campaigns.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>

        <article class="nt-frame-row">
            <div class="nt-frame-copy">
                <div class="num">03<span class="slash">/</span><span class="lbl">Release content</span></div>
                <h3>Ship a walkthrough with every release.<br /><em>Not a blog post &mdash; a demo.</em></h3>
                <p>Record a NavTour of each new feature the day it ships. Embed it in the announcement email, release notes, and in-app notifications. Users feel the value, not just read about it.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>From capture to published demo in under 15 minutes</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Bilingual EN/ES in one pass with AI translation</li>
                    <li><span class="chk">&#10003;</span>Analytics on which features drive the most engagement</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="nt-frame-visual">
                <span class="nt-frame-cap">Product release &middot; feature demo</span>
                <div class="nt-frame-img">
                    <img src="/images/shots/editor.png" alt="NavTour editor for release demo creation" class="nt-lightbox" />
                </div>
                <div class="anno tr">
                    <div class="lbl">Release cadence</div>
                    <strong>Feature content that ships with the feature</strong>
                    <p>No more &ldquo;we&rsquo;ll do a video later&rdquo; that never happens.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>

<NtCTABand Headline="Embed your first interactive demo by end of day."
           SubText="No engineering time, no design sprint. The Chrome extension captures your product in 2 minutes."
           PrimaryLabel="Start free &rarr;"
           SecondaryLabel="See all solutions"
           SecondaryHref="/solutions" />
